{"add":{"doc":{"id":"43d437182b5051833aa54db6628027930f2f5f49e84a0894c1f7056c8f39055b","url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f0/Portrait_of_Susan_B._Anthony.jpg/220px-Portrait_of_Susan_B._Anthony.jpg","previous":[],"after":["As a teen, Anthony went to parties, and she had offers of marriage when she was older, but there is no record of her ever having a serious romance.[164] Anthony loved children, however, and helped raise the children in the Stanton household.[16] Referring to her niece, she wrote, \"The dear little Lucy engrosses most of my time and thoughts. A child one loves is a constant benediction to the soul, whether or not it helps to the accomplishment of great intellectual feats.\"[165]"]}}}